The paper discusses the challenges of reusing Linked Open Data (LOD) for various tasks, which involves issues related to semantic heterogeneity, provenance, and data quality. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), and software engineering (cs.SE). Among these, cs.AI and cs.DB are the most likely categories, as the paper discusses the use of LOD as background knowledge for supporting AI tasks and the challenges of data quality and provenance, which are central to database research.
